# Test Case Management (Staged Implementation)

When you **complete implementation for a stage**, add the corresponding test cases to **tests/test-stages.py** as specified in [docs/progress.md](docs/progress.md) and [docs/prd.md](docs/prd.md).

## Workflow

1. After implementing a stage, open [docs/progress.md](docs/progress.md) for the stage list and runnable commands, and [docs/prd.md](docs/prd.md) for behavior and decisions.
2. Implement each test case listed there as one or more pytest test functions.
3. Add them to **tests/test-stages.py**, grouped by stage (e.g. a class `TestStage2MessageBus` or a module-level comment `# --- Stage N ---` and tests below it).
4. Use pytest conventions: `test_*` names, assert expectations; mock external deps (Milvus, Neo4j, HTTP, etc.) so tests run without real services.

## File layout

- **Single file:** `tests/test-stages.py` holds all stage tests.
- **Organization:** Group tests by stage number/name so the file stays scannable (e.g. Stage 2 block, then Stage 3 block).
- **Stage 1:** progress.md specifies a runnable CLI check only; no pytest for Stage 1.1 unless you add a smoke test.

## Reference

Use [docs/progress.md](docs/progress.md) for work breakdown and runnable commands; [docs/prd.md](docs/prd.md) for what to test. Run with `pytest tests/test-stages.py -v` (or `-k stage_2`).
